getTotalColumns

public int getTotalColumns()
Description copied from class: Term
Get the total number of columns needed to represent this term. Objects and variables only need one column: the name of the term. Term functions need one column for their name, and then the sum of the needed columns for each of their arguments.

Specified by:
getTotalColumns in class Term
Returns:
The total number of columns needed to represent this term.

hasVariable

public boolean hasVariable(TermVariable variable)
Checks whether the function contains references to the input variable. Used for unification of a variable and a function ('occurs' check).

Parameters:
variable - The variable whose presence to check for.
Returns:
True if variable appears anywhere within the function's arguments.
